{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|艸|戊|c1=s|c2=p|t1=grass|ls=psc}}.

Applying this character to mean “[[cyclopentadiene]]” in organic chemistry results from the decomposition of the character as an {{Han compound|艸|戊|t1=radical for [[aromatic]] compounds|t2=five-carbon ring|ls=ic|nocap=1}}, since the [[conjugate base]] of cyclopentadiene (cyclopentadienyl anion) is aromatic.
